The genus 'Planes' currently comprises three extant species: [[Planes minutus]] (Linnaeus, 1758), [[Planes marinus]]
Rathbun, 1914, and [[Planes major]] (=cyaneus) (MacLeay, 1838). A further fossil
species is known from the Middle Miocene of the
Caucasus.
